    <text id="A5515T">
        <front id="d2">
            <div1 id="d3" type="summary">
                <p>John McCue sends a promise to pay $43.50 to hire a slave girl from Mrs.
                    Carrington for one year.</p>
            </div1>
        </front>

        <body id="d4">
            <div1 id="d5" type="letter">
                <opener>
                    <dateline> McCue to Carrington <date value="1854-01-02">1854</date>
                    </dateline>

                </opener>

                <p>"Twelve months after date I promise to pay Mrs Mary Carrington the just and full
                    sum of Forty three Dollars &amp; fifty cents it being for the hire of Sally,
                    a negro girl belonging to the sd Mary Carrington, the said hiring to date and
                    take effect from the 2nd of Jany 1854 and to determine the 25th of Decr. of the
                    same year, at which time the sd servant is to be returned to the sd Mrs Mary
                    Carrington at Fleetwood in the Co. of Nelson. The taxes of sd girl are to be pd
                    by me and the usual clothing furnished during the term, and when returned. In
                    witness whereof, I have unto set my hand &amp; seal this 2nd of Jan'y 1854. </p>

                <closer>

                    <signed>J[?][?].</signed>
                </closer>
            </div1>
        </body>
    </text>
